1. Java Concurrency Fundamentals
BlockingQueue: Thread-safe queue for producer-consumer patterns

ExecutorService: Thread pool management

Runnable Interface: Creating tasks that run in separate threads

Thread Safety: Preventing race conditions and data corruption

2. Design Patterns
Producer-Consumer Pattern: One thread produces work, another consumes it

Thread Pool Pattern: Reusing threads for better performance

Queue-based Processing: Decoupling request handling from processing

3. Database Concepts
ACID Properties: Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability

Transaction Management: Ensuring data consistency

Audit Trails: Tracking changes for compliance







